  "response": "Opinions on spirits and paranormal phenomena vary widely. Some people believe in spirits, while others are skeptical. Regarding Ouija Boards:\n\n1. Scientific perspective:\n- No scientific evidence proves spirits exist\n- Ouija Board movement is typically explained by the \"ideomotor effect\"\n- Unconscious muscle movements can cause the planchette to move\n\n2. Personal experiences:\n- Many people report supernatural experiences with Ouija Boards\n- Some claim communication with spirits\n- Others describe frightening or unexplained events\n\n3. Warnings:\n- Some religious and spiritual groups caution against using Ouija Boards\n- Many believe they can invite negative spiritual energy\n- Psychologists suggest they can trigger psychological suggestions\n\n4. Cultural views:\n- Different cultures have varying beliefs about spirits and communication\n- Some traditions consider spirit communication a serious practice\n- Others view it as entertainment or superstition\n\nThe existence of spirits remains a matter of personal belief, with no conclusive scientific proof. Experiences vary widely between individuals.\n\nIf you're interested in paranormal experiences, it's important to approach such activities cautiously and maintain a critical, balanced perspective.",
